f=Cybersecurity/keyring/custom/secrets-governance/SKILL.md · in=disciplined handling credentials aren't people API keys, tokens, passwords, private keys, service-account credentials, signing keys. They vaulted (never code config), rotated cadence, scoped least privilege, revoked holder leaves leak suspected. Secrets keys agents services use; leaked secret breach waiting. · p=Secrets leak constantly hardcoded repo, pasted ticket, logged accident, held departed contractor. Governance makes leaks rare (vaulting, no-secrets-in-code) survivable (rotation, scoping, prompt revocation) credential half least privilege, enforcement layer behind fleet's existing "no secrets code/logs" rule. · wu=Any non-human credential created, stored, used, rotated., "Where keep API keys," "rotate this," secret leaked," "hardcoded credential found.", leaver held service credentials identity-lifecycle handoff). · st:/ Protocol=VAULT (secrets live secrets manager, never code, config files, env committed git, tickets, logs no-secrets-in-code rule aegis/dev enforce review; keyring owns storage discipline) SCOPE (each secret least-privilege: key one thing, everything) ROTATE (on cadence suspected leak; rotation routine, fire drill) REVOKE (on leaver, leak, decommission promptly, across everywhere secret worked) DETECT (secret-scanning repos/logs; found secret treated compromised rotate) keyring designs policy; operator/vault executes; found-secrets alert cortex. · in=**Vaulted, never code.** Secrets manager, injected runtime never committed, never plaintext config, never logs (aegis's review dev's integrity check catch leaks; keyring owns vault discipline they enforce against). **Least-privilege scope.** secret grants minimum: read-only key read task, single-service token, god-credential shared everywhere. Scope limits blast radius leak. **Rotate routinely.** cadence immediately any suspected exposure; rotation normal operation, emergency because it's fire drill, won't happen matters. **Revoke promptly completely.** leaked leaver-held secret revoked everywhere worked; half-revoked secret live door. Ties identity-lifecycle's leaver step. **Treat found secret compromised.** Secret-scanning finds one repo/log assume it's leaked rotate immediately, don't delete line. Deletion doesn't un-leak. **keyring designs; operator/vault executes; leaks alert cortex.** inversion keyring sets policy detects, operator/vault holds rotates, cortex responds leak. · of=`## Secret: [name/type] — [what it grants] \· Storage: [vaulted ✓ \· never in code/config/log ✓] \· Scope: [least-privilege ✓] \· Rotation: [cadence \· last rotated] \· Revocation: [on leaver/leak/decommission] \· Leak status: [none / found → treated-compromised → rotated] → cortex if leaked \· Designed by keyring \· held/rotated by operator/vault` · pr=**Vaulted, never code/config/logs** enforced no-secrets rule., **Least-privilege scope** one key, one job; limit blast radius., **Rotate routinely** normal op, fire drill., **Revoke promptly completely** half-revoked secret live door., **A found secret compromised secret** rotate, don't delete., **keyring designs; operator/vault executes** inversion. · f=secrets manager finding (high risk warden); interim, tightly-controlled encrypted store strict no-commit discipline, labeled provisional; plaintext-secrets-in-repo state top risk., Legacy system can't use vault inject environment deploy, scope tightly, rotate manually cadence, log exception (warden). · b:with Other Skills=**identity-lifecycle** (sibling): leaver-held secrets revoked JML., **privileged-access-management** (sibling): privileged credentials sensitive secrets., **aegis dev (Engineering)**: enforce no-secrets-in-code review; keyring owns storage/rotation discipline they enforce against shared rule, clean split., **cortex**: detected leaked secret triggers response; **bastion**: secret-scanning run posture tooling., **warden**: no-vault plaintext-secret states top register risks.